{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I grew up in Northern Ireland, right up in the"},{"time":2000,"text":"very, very north end of it there,"},{"time":4000,"text":"where it's absolutely freezing cold."},{"time":7000,"text":"This was me running around in the back garden mid-summer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11000,"text":"I couldn't pick a career."},{"time":12000,"text":"In Ireland the obvious choice is the military,"},{"time":14000,"text":"but to be honest it actually kind of sucks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"My mother wanted me to be a dentist."},{"time":22000,"text":"But the problem was that people kept blowing everything up."},{"time":24000,"text":"So I actually went to school in Belfast,"},{"time":26000,"text":"which was where all the action happened."},{"time":28000,"text":"And this was a pretty common sight."},{"time":30000,"text":"The school I went to was pretty boring."},{"time":32000,"text":"They forced us to learn things like Latin."},{"time":35000,"text":"The school teachers weren't having much fun,"},{"time":37000,"text":"the sports were very dirty or very painful."},{"time":39000,"text":"So I cleverly chose rowing, which I got very good at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"And I was actually rowing for my school here"},{"time":44000,"text":"until this fateful day, and I flipped over right in front"},{"time":47000,"text":"of the entire school."},{"time":48000,"text":"And that was the finishing post right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"So this was extremely embarrassing."},{"time":52000,"text":"But our school at that time got a grant from the government,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and they got an incredible computer -- the research machine 3DZ --"},{"time":57000,"text":"and they left the programming manuals lying around."},{"time":61000,"text":"And so students like myself with nothing to do,"},{"time":63000,"text":"we would learn how to program it."},{"time":65000,"text":"Also around this time, at home,"},{"time":67000,"text":"this was the computer that people were buying."},{"time":68000,"text":"It was called the Sinclair ZX80. This was a 1K computer,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and you'd buy your programs on cassette tape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"Actually I'm just going to pause for one second,"},{"time":76000,"text":"because I heard that there's a prerequisite to speak here at TED --"},{"time":78000,"text":"you had to have a picture of yourself from the old days with big hair."},{"time":81000,"text":"So I brought a picture with big hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"(Laughter)."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"I just want to get that out of the way."},{"time":86000,"text":"So after the Sinclair ZX80 came along the very cleverly named"},{"time":90000,"text":"Sinclair ZX81."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"And -- you see the picture at the bottom?"},{"time":94000,"text":"There's a picture of a guy doing homework with his son."},{"time":96000,"text":"That's what they thought they had built it for."},{"time":99000,"text":"The reality is we got the programming manual"},{"time":101000,"text":"and we started making games for it."},{"time":102000,"text":"We were programming in BASIC,"},{"time":103000,"text":"which is a pretty awful language for games,"},{"time":105000,"text":"so we ended up learning Assembly language"},{"time":107000,"text":"so we could really take control of the hardware."},{"time":110000,"text":"This is the guy that invented it, Sir Clive Sinclair,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and he's showing his machine."},{"time":113000,"text":"You had this same thing in America,"},{"time":115000,"text":"it was called the Timex Sinclair1000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"To play a game in those days you had to have an imagination"},{"time":120000,"text":"to believe that you were really playing \"Battlestar Galactica.\""},{"time":123000,"text":"The graphics were just horrible."},{"time":126000,"text":"You had to have an even better imagination to play this game,"},{"time":128000,"text":"\"Death Rider.\""},{"time":129000,"text":"But of course the scientists couldn't help themselves."},{"time":131000,"text":"They started making their own video games."},{"time":134000,"text":"This is one of my favorite ones here, where they have rabbit breeding,"},{"time":138000,"text":"so males choose the lucky rabbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"It was around this time we went from 1K to 16K,"},{"time":143000,"text":"which was quite the leap."},{"time":145000,"text":"And if you're wondering how much 16K is,"},{"time":147000,"text":"this eBay logo here is 16K."},{"time":149000,"text":"And in that amount of memory someone programmed"},{"time":152000,"text":"a full flight simulation program."},{"time":154000,"text":"And that's what it looked like."},{"time":156000,"text":"I spent ages flying this flight simulator,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and I honestly believed I could fly airplanes by the end of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"Here's Clive Sinclair now launching his color computer."},{"time":166000,"text":"He's recognized as being the father of video games in Europe."},{"time":169000,"text":"He's a multi-millionaire, and I think that's why he's"},{"time":171000,"text":"smiling in this photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"So I went on for the next 20 years or so"},{"time":175000,"text":"making a lot of different games."},{"time":177000,"text":"Some of the highlights were things like \"The Terminator,\""},{"time":179000,"text":"\"Aladdin,\" the \"Teenage Mutant Hero Turtles.\""},{"time":182000,"text":"Because I was from the United Kingdom,"},{"time":183000,"text":"they thought the word ninja was a little too mean for children,"},{"time":187000,"text":"so they decided to call it hero instead."},{"time":189000,"text":"I personally preferred the Spanish version,"},{"time":191000,"text":"which was \"Tortugas Ninja.\""},{"time":193000,"text":"That was much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"Then the last game I did was based on trying to get the video game industry"},{"time":201000,"text":"and Hollywood to actually work together on something --"},{"time":204000,"text":"instead of licensing from each other, to actually work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"Now, Chris did ask me to bring some statistics with me,"},{"time":209000,"text":"so I've done that."},{"time":211000,"text":"The video game industry in 2005 became a 29 billion dollar business."},{"time":215000,"text":"It grows every year."},{"time":216000,"text":"Last year was the biggest year."},{"time":218000,"text":"By 2008, we're going to kick the butt of the music industry."},{"time":221000,"text":"By 2010, we're going to hit 42 billion."},{"time":225000,"text":"43 percent of gamers are female."},{"time":227000,"text":"So there's a lot more female gamers than people are really aware."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"The average age of gamers?"},{"time":231000,"text":"Well, obviously it's for children, right?"},{"time":233000,"text":"Well, no, actually it's 30 years old."},{"time":234000,"text":"And interestingly, the people who buy the most games are 37."},{"time":238000,"text":"So 37 is our target audience."},{"time":241000,"text":"All video games are violent."},{"time":242000,"text":"Of course the newspapers love to beat on this."},{"time":245000,"text":"But 83 percent of games don't have any mature content whatsoever,"},{"time":249000,"text":"so it's just not true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"Online gaming statistics."},{"time":253000,"text":"I brought some stuff on \"World of Warcraft.\" It's 5.5 million players."},{"time":256000,"text":"It makes about 80 million bucks a month in subscriptions."},{"time":259000,"text":"It costs 50 bucks just to install it on your computer,"},{"time":262000,"text":"making the publisher about another 275 million."},{"time":266000,"text":"The game costs about 80 million dollars to make,"},{"time":268000,"text":"so basically it pays for itself in about a month."},{"time":270000,"text":"A player in a game called \"Project Entropia\""},{"time":273000,"text":"actually bought his own island for 26,500 dollars."},{"time":277000,"text":"You have to remember that this is not a real island."},{"time":279000,"text":"He didn't actually buy anything, just some data."},{"time":281000,"text":"But he got great terms on it."},{"time":283000,"text":"This purchase included mining and hunting rights,"},{"time":286000,"text":"ownership of all land on the island, and a castle"},{"time":288000,"text":"with no furniture included."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"This market is now estimated at over 800 million dollars annually."},{"time":295000,"text":"And what's interesting about it is the market was actually created"},{"time":297000,"text":"by the gamers themselves."},{"time":299000,"text":"They found clever ways to trade items"},{"time":301000,"text":"and to sell their accounts to each other"},{"time":303000,"text":"so that they could make money while they were playing their games."},{"time":305000,"text":"I dove onto eBay a couple of days ago"},{"time":307000,"text":"just to see what was gong on, typed in World of Warcraft, got 6,000 items."},{"time":311000,"text":"I liked this one the best:"},{"time":313000,"text":"a level 60 Warlock with lots of epics for 174,000 dollars."},{"time":317000,"text":"It's like that guy obviously had some pain while making it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"So as far as popularity of games,"},{"time":324000,"text":"what do you think these people are doing here?"},{"time":326000,"text":"It turns out they're actually in Hollywood Bowl in Los Angeles"},{"time":331000,"text":"listening to the L.A. Philharmonic playing video game music."},{"time":334000,"text":"That's what the show looks like."},{"time":335000,"text":"You would expect it to be cheesy, but it's not."},{"time":337000,"text":"It's very, very epic and a very beautiful concert."},{"time":339000,"text":"And the people that went there absolutely loved it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"What do you think these people are doing?"},{"time":343000,"text":"They're actually bringing their computers so they can play games"},{"time":345000,"text":"against each other."},{"time":347000,"text":"And this is happening in every city around the world."},{"time":349000,"text":"This is happening in your local cities too,"},{"time":351000,"text":"you're probably just not aware of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"Now, Chris told me that you had a timeline video a few years ago"},{"time":355000,"text":"here just to show how video game graphics have been improving."},{"time":359000,"text":"I wanted to update that video and give you a new look at it."},{"time":362000,"text":"But what I want you to do is to try to understand it."},{"time":364000,"text":"We're on this curve, and the graphics are getting"},{"time":366000,"text":"so ridiculously better."},{"time":368000,"text":"And I'm going to show you up to maybe 2007."},{"time":371000,"text":"But I want you to try and think about what games could look like"},{"time":373000,"text":"10 years from now."},{"time":375000,"text":"So we're going to start that video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"Video: Throughout human history people have played games."},{"time":381000,"text":"As man's intellect and technology have evolved"},{"time":384000,"text":"so too have the games he plays."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":527000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"David Perry: The thing again I want you to think about is,"},{"time":532000,"text":"don't look at these graphics and think of that's the way it is."},{"time":534000,"text":"Think about that's where we are right now,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and the curve that we're on means that this is going to continue"},{"time":538000,"text":"to get better."},{"time":540000,"text":"This is an example of the kind of graphics you need to be able to draw"},{"time":542000,"text":"if you wanted to get a job in the video game industry today."},{"time":545000,"text":"You need to be really an incredible artist."},{"time":547000,"text":"And once we get enough of those guys, we're going to want"},{"time":549000,"text":"more fantasy artists that can create places"},{"time":550000,"text":"we've never been to before, or characters that"},{"time":553000,"text":"we've just never seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"So the obvious thing for me to talk about today is graphics and audio."},{"time":558000,"text":"But if you were to go to a game developers conference,"},{"time":560000,"text":"what they're all talking about is emotion, purpose,"},{"time":562000,"text":"meaning, understanding and feeling."},{"time":564000,"text":"You'll hear about talks like, can a video game make you cry?"},{"time":567000,"text":"And these are the kind of topics we really actually care about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"I came across a student who's absolutely excellent"},{"time":573000,"text":"at expressing himself, and this student agreed"},{"time":576000,"text":"that he would not show his video to anybody until"},{"time":580000,"text":"you here at TED had seen it."},{"time":581000,"text":"So I'd like to play this video."},{"time":583000,"text":"So this is a student's opinion on what his experience of games are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"Video: I, like many of you, live somewhere between"},{"time":590000,"text":"reality and video games."},{"time":592000,"text":"Some part of me -- a true living, breathing person --"},{"time":596000,"text":"has become programmed, electronic and virtual."},{"time":600000,"text":"The boundary of my brain that divides real from fantasy"},{"time":602000,"text":"has finally begun to crumble."},{"time":605000,"text":"I'm a video game addict and this is my story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"In the year of my birth"},{"time":625000,"text":"the Nintendo Entertainment System also went into development."},{"time":634000,"text":"I played in the backyard, learned to read,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and even ate some of my vegetables."},{"time":638000,"text":"Most of my childhood was spent playing with Legos."},{"time":643000,"text":"But as was the case for most of my generation,"},{"time":645000,"text":"I spent a lot of time in front of the TV."},{"time":648000,"text":"Mr. Rogers, Walt Disney, Nick Junior,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and roughly half a million commercials have undoubtedly"},{"time":654000,"text":"left their mark on me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"When my parents bought my sister and I our first Nintendo,"},{"time":659000,"text":"whatever inherent addictive quality this early interactive"},{"time":663000,"text":"electronic entertainment possessed quickly took hold of me."},{"time":674000,"text":"At some point something clicked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"With the combination of simple, interactive stories"},{"time":685000,"text":"and the warmth of the TV set, my simple 16-bit Nintendo"},{"time":689000,"text":"became more than just an escape."},{"time":691000,"text":"It became an alternate existence, my virtual reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"I'm a video game addict, and it's not because of"},{"time":715000,"text":"a certain number of hours I have spent playing,"},{"time":716000,"text":"or nights I have gone without sleep to finish the next level."},{"time":720000,"text":"It is because I have had life-altering experiences in virtual space,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and video games had begun to erode my own understanding"},{"time":726000,"text":"of what is real and what is not."},{"time":730000,"text":"I'm addicted, because even though I know I'm losing my grip on reality,"},{"time":733000,"text":"I still crave more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"From an early age I learned to invest myself emotionally"},{"time":749000,"text":"in what unfolded before me on screen."},{"time":752000,"text":"Today, after 20 years of watching TV geared to make me emotional,"},{"time":756000,"text":"even a decent insurance commercial can bring tears to my eyes."},{"time":764000,"text":"I am just one of a new generation that is growing up."},{"time":767000,"text":"A generation who may experience much more meaning"},{"time":770000,"text":"through video games than they will through the real world."},{"time":774000,"text":"Video games are nearing an evolutionary leap,"},{"time":776000,"text":"a point where game worlds will look and feel just as real"},{"time":779000,"text":"as the films we see in theatres, or the news we watch on TV."},{"time":782000,"text":"And while my sense of free will in these virtual worlds"},{"time":784000,"text":"may still be limited, what I do learn applies to my real life."},{"time":789000,"text":"Play enough video games and eventually you will"},{"time":791000,"text":"really believe you can snowboard, fly a plane,"},{"time":794000,"text":"drive a nine-second quarter mile, or kill a man."},{"time":798000,"text":"I know I can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"Unlike any pop culture phenomenon before it,"},{"time":808000,"text":"video games actually allow us to become part of the machine."},{"time":810000,"text":"They allow us to sublimate into the culture of interactive,"},{"time":813000,"text":"downloaded, streaming, HD reality."},{"time":817000,"text":"We are interacting with our entertainment."},{"time":820000,"text":"I have come to expect this level of interaction."},{"time":822000,"text":"Without it, the problems faced in the real world --"},{"time":825000,"text":"poverty, war, disease and genocide -- lack the levity they should."},{"time":831000,"text":"Their importance blends into the sensationalized drama"},{"time":833000,"text":"of prime time TV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"But the beauty of video games today lies not in the lifelike graphics,"},{"time":839000,"text":"the vibrating joysticks or virtual surround sound."},{"time":843000,"text":"It lies in that these games are beginning to make me emotional."},{"time":847000,"text":"I have fought in wars, feared for my own survival,"},{"time":850000,"text":"watched my cohorts die on beaches and woods that look and feel"},{"time":854000,"text":"more real than any textbook or any news story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"The people who create these games are smart."},{"time":860000,"text":"They know what makes me scared, excited, panicked, proud or sad."},{"time":864000,"text":"Then they use these emotions to dimensionalize the worlds they create."},{"time":868000,"text":"A well-designed video game will seamlessly"},{"time":870000,"text":"weave the user into the fabric of the virtual experience."},{"time":873000,"text":"As one becomes more experienced"},{"time":875000,"text":"the awareness of physical control melts away."},{"time":878000,"text":"I know what I want and I do it."},{"time":880000,"text":"No buttons to push, no triggers to pull, just me and the game."},{"time":885000,"text":"My fate and the fate of the world around me lie inside my hands."},{"time":893000,"text":"I know violent video games make my mother worry."},{"time":896000,"text":"What troubles me is not that video game violence"},{"time":898000,"text":"is becoming more and more like real life violence,"},{"time":901000,"text":"but that real life violence is starting to look more and more"},{"time":904000,"text":"like a video game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"These are all troubles outside of myself."},{"time":916000,"text":"I, however, have a problem very close to home."},{"time":918000,"text":"Something has happened to my brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"Perhaps there is a single part of our brain that holds"},{"time":934000,"text":"all of our gut instincts, the things we know to do"},{"time":936000,"text":"before we even think."},{"time":938000,"text":"While some of these instincts may be innate, most are learned,"},{"time":941000,"text":"and all of them are hardwired into our brains."},{"time":944000,"text":"These instincts are essential for survival in both real and virtual worlds."},{"time":954000,"text":"Only in recent years has the technology behind video games"},{"time":956000,"text":"allowed for a true overlap in stimuli."},{"time":960000,"text":"As gamers we are now living by the same laws of physics"},{"time":963000,"text":"in the same cities and doing many of the same things"},{"time":965000,"text":"we once did in real life, only virtually."},{"time":969000,"text":"Consider this --"},{"time":971000,"text":"my real life car has about 25,000 miles on it."},{"time":974000,"text":"In all my driving games, I've driven a total of 31,459 miles."},{"time":979000,"text":"To some degree I've learned how to drive from the game."},{"time":982000,"text":"The sensory cues are very similar."},{"time":984000,"text":"It's a funny feeling when you have spent more time"},{"time":986000,"text":"doing something on the TV than you have in real life."},{"time":990000,"text":"When I am driving down a road at sunset all I can think is,"},{"time":993000,"text":"this is almost as beautiful as my games are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996000,"text":"For my virtual worlds are perfect."},{"time":998000,"text":"More beautiful and rich than the real world around us."},{"time":1001000,"text":"I'm not sure what the implications of my experience are,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"but the potential for using realistic video game stimuli in repetition"},{"time":1008000,"text":"on a vast number of loyal participants is frightening to me."},{"time":1012000,"text":"Today I believe Big Brother would find much more success"},{"time":1015000,"text":"brainwashing the masses with video games"},{"time":1017000,"text":"rather than just simply TVs."},{"time":1020000,"text":"Video games are fun, engaging, and leave your brain"},{"time":1023000,"text":"completely vulnerable to re-programming."},{"time":1027000,"text":"But maybe brainwashing isn't always bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030000,"text":"Imagine a game that teaches us to respect each other,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"or helps us to understand the problems we're all facing"},{"time":1035000,"text":"in the real world."},{"time":1036000,"text":"There is a potential to do good as well."},{"time":1040000,"text":"It is critical, as these virtual worlds continue to mirror"},{"time":1042000,"text":"the real world we live in, that game developers realize"},{"time":1045000,"text":"that they have tremendous responsibilities before them."},{"time":1048000,"text":"I'm not sure what the future of video games holds"},{"time":1051000,"text":"for our civilization."},{"time":1052000,"text":"But as virtual and real world experiences increasingly overlap"},{"time":1056000,"text":"there is a greater and greater potential for other people"},{"time":1058000,"text":"to feel the same way I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062000,"text":"What I have only recently come to realize"},{"time":1064000,"text":"is that beyond the graphics, sound, game play and emotion"},{"time":1068000,"text":"it is the power to break down reality that is so fascinating"},{"time":1071000,"text":"and addictive to me."},{"time":1073000,"text":"I know that I am losing my grip."},{"time":1075000,"text":"Part of me is just waiting to let go."},{"time":1082000,"text":"I know though, that no matter how amazing video games may become,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"or how flat the real world may seem to us,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"that we must stay aware of what our games are teaching us"},{"time":1091000,"text":"and how they leave us feeling when we finally do unplug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100000,"text":"DP: Wow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108000,"text":"I found that video very, very thought provoking,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"and that's why I wanted to bring it here for you guys to see."},{"time":1113000,"text":"And what was interesting about it is the obvious choice"},{"time":1115000,"text":"for me to talk about was graphics and audio."},{"time":1118000,"text":"But as you heard, Michael talked about all these other elements as well."},{"time":1122000,"text":"Video games give an awful lot of other things too,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"and that's why people get so addicted."},{"time":1125000,"text":"The most important one being fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127000,"text":"The name of this track is \"The Magic To Come.\""},{"time":1129000,"text":"Who is that going to come from?"},{"time":1130000,"text":"Is it going to come from the best directors in the world"},{"time":1132000,"text":"as we thought it probably would?"},{"time":1133000,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":1134000,"text":"I think it's going to come from the children who are growing up now"},{"time":1137000,"text":"that aren't stuck with all of the stuff that we remember from the past."},{"time":1142000,"text":"They're going to do it their way, using the tools that we've created."},{"time":1144000,"text":"The same with students or highly creative people,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"writers and people like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150000,"text":"As far as colleges go, there's about 350 colleges around the world"},{"time":1152000,"text":"teaching video game courses."},{"time":1155000,"text":"That means there's literally thousands of new ideas."},{"time":1158000,"text":"Some of the ideas are really dreadful and some of them are great."},{"time":1161000,"text":"There's nothing worse than having to listen to someone"},{"time":1163000,"text":"try and pitch you a really bad video game idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1165000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171000,"text":"Chris Anderson: You're off, you're off. That's it."},{"time":1173000,"text":"He's out of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176000,"text":"DP: I've just got a little tiny bit more if you'll indulge me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178000,"text":"CA: Go ahead. I'm going to stay right here though."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1181000,"text":"DP: This is just a cool shot, because this is students coming to school after class."},{"time":1184000,"text":"The school is closed; they're coming back at midnight"},{"time":1187000,"text":"because they want to pitch their video game ideas."},{"time":1189000,"text":"I'm sitting at the front of the class,"},{"time":1190000,"text":"and they're actually pitching their ideas."},{"time":1192000,"text":"So it's hard to get students to come back to class,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"but it is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1195000,"text":"This is my daughter, her name's Emma, she's 17 months old."},{"time":1198000,"text":"And I've been asking myself, what is Emma going to experience"},{"time":1201000,"text":"in the video game world?"},{"time":1203000,"text":"And as I've shown here, we have the audience."},{"time":1206000,"text":"She's never going to know a world where you can't press a button"},{"time":1209000,"text":"and have millions of people ready to play."},{"time":1211000,"text":"You know, we have the technology."},{"time":1213000,"text":"She's never going to know a world where the graphics just aren't"},{"time":1215000,"text":"stunning and really immersive."},{"time":1217000,"text":"And as the student video showed, we can impact and move."},{"time":1220000,"text":"She's never going to know a world where video games"},{"time":1222000,"text":"aren't incredibly emotional and will probably make her cry."},{"time":1225000,"text":"I just hope she likes video games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1228000,"text":"So, my closing thought."},{"time":1229000,"text":"Games on the surface seem simple entertainment,"},{"time":1231000,"text":"but for those that like to look a little deeper,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"the new paradigm of video games could open entirely new frontiers"},{"time":1236000,"text":"to creative minds that like to think big."},{"time":1239000,"text":"Where better to challenge those minds than here at TED?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1241000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1242000,"text":"Chris Anderson: David Perry. That was awesome."}]}]}